INSERT INTO `_WPI_posts` VALUES (149,3,'2019-07-26 21:44:36','2019-07-26 21:44:36','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>SUCCESS AND SIGNIFICANCE these are two words that could be used to encompass what almost all people strive for. But, is there a single metric? Is there a single ubiquitous view point of these two identity defining nouns? </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I used to judge my success by how well (or poorly) I lived up to t<em>he projections of what others expected of me</em>. Parents, friends, mentors, peers, significant others --- you name it; they all have expectations for who and what we are meant to be. And, <em>we have the same expectations of others that we project onto them.</em> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For me, at first, it was how devout a Catholic I was, how well at school I was doing, how I was faring against my parents dreams and standards of me. My definition of success was an amalgamation of what they thought was best for me. But, <em>being GREAT means defining what is best for yourself</em>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Being <em>GREAT </em>for me starts with staying true to what I think is right for my work and understanding how that work can impact those around me. Let me tell you: you don\'t need to seek approval or validation. You should be staying true to your vision because inevitably it will inspire those around you to be true to themselves.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My definition of SUCCESS and SIGNIFICANCE is measured by how well I am impacting the lives around me. <em>Am I a positive influence in my circle and in the circles that I have the good fortune of sharing a space with? Am I doing what I can to push my friends and family? Do I want better for them? Am I Challenging them to be better?</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For my entire life it was so easy to just focus on myself and strive for being enough to satisfy the expectations that were thrust upon me. But, during my time in my undergraduate studies I started thinking about what success is worth if the people around me are <em>suffering and cold</em>. I know that sometimes in life it feels like even though <em>there are 12 billion hands on this planet that not one of them is extended to your vicinity, literally</em>. <em>(Shout-out NAK) </em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, my mantra is that we gotta do what we can not to just bring food to the table but to make sure that the table is big enough for everyone to be able to take a seat. I try to be significant in others lives by trying to be the person that I wish I had when I was going through the struggle. A person that could talk me through it, guide me through it, and tell it to me straight. To me, if you\'re the only one on your team that is eating while the rest fight for scraps then you aren\'t great. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>SUCCESS and SIGNIFICANCE through a cooperative and compassionate humanistic lens is what I strive for and what I think GREATNESS is. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now what do you think makes you GREAT and how do you measure yourself<em>?</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','What Makes You Great?','In this blog post Alec expands on his definition and measure of success and significance.','inherit','closed','closed','','102-revision-v1','','','2019-07-26 21:44:36','2019-07-26 21:44:36','',102,'http://born-great.local/2019/07/26/102-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
