self and strive for being enough to satisfy the expectations that were thrust upon me. But, during my time in my undergraduate studies I started thinking about what success is worth if the people around me are <em>suffering and cold</em>. I know firsthand that sometimes in life it feels like even though <em>there are 12 billion hands on this planet that not one of them is extended to your vicinity, literally</em>. <em>(Shout-out NAK) </em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So, my mantra is that <strong>we can\'t just bring food to the table, we have to make sure that the table is big enough for everyone to take a seat.</strong> I try to be significant in others lives by trying to be the person that I wish I had when I was going through the struggle. A person that could talk me through it, guide me through it, and tell it to me straight. To me, if you\'re the only one on your team that\'s eating while the rest fight for scraps then you aren\'t great. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>SUCCESS and SIGNIFICANCE through a cooperative and compassionate humanistic lens is what I strive for and what I think GREATNESS is. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now what do you think makes you GREAT and how do you measure yourself<em>?</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','What Makes You Great?','In this blog post Alec expands on his definition and measure of success and significance.','inherit','closed','closed','','102-revision-v1','','','2019-07-26 21:57:56','2019-07-26 21:57:56','',102,'http://born-great.local/2019/07/26/102-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
