INSERT INTO `_WPI_posts` VALUES (182,6,'2019-09-04 06:57:31','2019-09-04 06:57:31','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Originally posted September 14, 2018 on my personal blog.</em> <em>This post was written during my time as a legal intern for Nevada Legal Services, a nonprofit that services Nevadans under the poverty line</em>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During the summer of 2018, I interned at Nevada Legal Services, a nonprofit that services Nevadans under the poverty line for legal experience. I was expecting another struggle to get through the work day from one podcast episode to the next while filling out unemployment briefs. When I walked in, two of our lead attorneys were angrily yelling. Not at each other, but at something. When I walked in, they just said, \"We\'re going to Pahrump.\" To give you an idea of Pahrump, the Mayor of Pahrump owns a brothel and calls himself the \"Trump of Pahrump.\" The reason the drive was warranted was because the local Nye County Sheriff\'s Deputies raided a local homeless encampment call \"The Hill\" consisting of around 40-50 people in abandoned land. As expected, it is located up a desert dirt hill composed of RV\'s, tents, cars, and trailers. The nonprofit I volunteer for was listening to their stories and formalizing them into some formal action to aid this community.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The camp itself is around 7-8 years old, but this was not their first time being forced out of the land. Five years ago, the camp was threatened to be bulldozed by developers, but the then residents were just warned to move further back. The land was believed to be property of the Bureau of Land Management, which is an agency that handles and auctions land on the behalf of the federal government. It\'s pretty common practice, especially in Nevada where much land is unsold or underdeveloped outside of the major cities. After the initial incident, there has not been a single w