INSERT INTO `_WPI_posts` VALUES (227,6,'2019-10-31 05:26:51','2019-10-31 05:26:51','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In 1994, rapper Common put out the song called \"I Used to Love H.E.R.\" that is still celebrated today as one of hip-hop\'s rare treasures. In the song, Common raps about a fading love with a women for her intellect and social awareness, before losing her conscious mindset to the rise of gangsta lifestyle and culture. The song is widely acclaimed as a classic because it mirrors his personal relationship with the hip hop genre with H.E.R. standing for \"Hip-Hop in its Essence is Real.\" Lyrics and themes from this song can be seen in KanYe West\'s, Ms. Lauryn Hill, Pro Era, and countless other hip hop songs. Common did not just produce a song, but actually reflected a more general, nostalgic opinion about hip hop. Like Common, I share this same love and wanted to share 10 songs that made me fall in love with H.E.R. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Dear Mama\" by 2Pac </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"I Wonder\" by Kanye West </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Can I Kick it\" by Tribe Called Quest</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Faithful\" by Common</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Juicy\" by The Notorious B.I.G.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"fontSize\":\"medium\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-medium-font-size\"><strong>\"Sing about Me, I\'m Dying of Thirst\" by Kendrick Lamar</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Kendrick Lamar is a true enigma to reach some where in that rare space of artists receiving global co<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">mmercial acclaim and authentic respect from his predecessors and mentors for unique production and strong lyrical presence.</span> This song and more generally, <em>good kid m.A.A.d. city</em> are demonstrations of why he deserves such <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">attention</span>. This song carries heavy significance in my life, so I will be breaking down every part of this song verse by verse nearly. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Sing about Me\" is the first part of this introspective epoch speaking about life in an urban ghetto, the positive and negative effects of his music, and how he himself copes with this responsibility as an artist. Each verse takes a different perspective with the first two as people speaking to Kendrick and the last verse as Kendrick\'s own response to both individuals and more generally us as an audience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verse1</strong>: This verse takes a perspective of a man that is speaking directly to Kendrick to say final words before embarking to avenge his dead brother. Through this verse, Kendrick dives into the violence that he experienced and witness growing up through the voice of another. Verse1 is greatly troubled by the mental trauma caused the death of his younger brother: \"My mind is really distorted / I find nothing but trouble in my life.\" After losing his brother, Verse1 is obligated to pass the same fate to people responsible, rather fulfilling a self-destroying prophecy of reactionary eye for an eye. Despite the darkness of this verse, one telling point is Verse1 states, \"I\'m fortunate you believe in a dream.\" Through Kendrick\'s music, Verse1 and his brother will live forever, so he finds solace in the rapper telling his story to others. Tragically, the last bars: \"And if I die before your album drop, I hope— [Gunshots]\" communicate that Verse1 never made it to see Kendrick\'s first album.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Verse2</strong>: This verse takes the perspective of a woman angry at Kendrick about how her sister is portrayed in \"Keisha\'s Song\" from <em>Section 80</em>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','The 10 Songs that Made me Fall in Love with Hip-Hop','','publish','open','open','','the-10-songs-that-made-me-fall-in-love-with-hip-hop','','','2019-10-31 05:26:51','2019-10-31 05:26:51','',0,'http://born-great.local/?p=227',0,'post','',0);
